{"article_id":"Tgqt4OmsqXq0Y4sn","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"In a stunning turn , Senate Republicans","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"- in the dead of night , on their last hope","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"of passing any kind of Obamacare repeal bill -","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"came up short .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"The result is , for now , a crushing blow to seven years of promises","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"to uproot the health care law .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"Three Republican senators","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"- Susan Collins of Maine , John McCain of Arizona , and Lisa Murkowski of Alaska -","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"voted to block the Senate ' s so-called \" skinny \" repeal bill .","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"It was the bare minimum :","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"The bill failed on a procedural vote , 49 to 51 .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"All three senators had their reasons ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"and they had each hinted for weeks","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"that they would be reluctant to back the Senate ' s various Obamacare repeal proposals .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"By the wee hours of Friday morning , three different Senate plans","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"- a robust repeal-and-replace bill , a cleaner repeal bill , and finally so-called skinny repeal -","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"had failed over three days of debate .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"Collins and Murkowski voted down all three .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"They had said for two months","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"that they wouldn ' t support a plan","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"that resulted in millions fewer Americans","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"having health coverage .","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"The three health care bills","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"that Republicans tried to pass","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"would have led to between 16 million and 32 million fewer Americans","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"having health insurance ,","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"when compared to Obamacare .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"McCain , though , was the surprise .","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"Diagnosed with brain cancer and the subject of much speculation after a rousing Senate speech","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"calling for a return to an open and bipartisan process in the Senate ,","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"the Arizona Republican joined the other Republican dissenters at the climax of the Senate health care fight","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"- and helped kill the bill .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"The stunning defeat in the Senate leaves the GOP ' s hopes for Obamacare repeal hanging by a thread .","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"Republicans have been here before in the past seven months ,","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"and their attempts have always come back from the dead .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"But in the course of a week , Senate leadership came up with three different plans","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"to try to achieve the goal","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"of repealing Obamacare ,","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"and they fell short every time .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"In the past three days , enough Republicans refused to vote","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"to roll back Obamacare ' s expanded health insurance coverage .","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"Then , at the last moment , one more senator decided","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"that the rushed and secretive process","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"- a process","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"decried even by Republicans","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"who still voted to support it -","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"was unacceptable .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"Republicans refused to vote","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"to roll back Obamacare ' s coverage gains","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Collins and Murkowski have made clear for weeks","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"that simply undoing what Obamacare had accomplished","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"- coverage gains , expanded Medicaid , protections for people with preexisting conditions -","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"was unacceptable .","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"\" I want greater access and lower costs .","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"So far , I 'm not seeing that happen , \"","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"Murkowski told me in mid-June .","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"Her state ,","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"though it struggles with the highest health care costs in the country ,","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"has expanded Medicaid","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"to cover its poorest residents","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"and has seen tens of thousands of people sign up for private coverage .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"Every plan","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"Republicans put forward","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"was projected to result in millions fewer people having insurance","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"and out-of-pocket costs rising .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"`` I can not support a bill","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"that is going to result in tens of millions of people losing their health insurance , \"","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"she said last month .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"The math on each of the Senate GOP plans was clear .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"Repeal and replace :","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"22 million more uninsured .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"Repeal only :","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"32 million .","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"\" Skinny \" repeal :","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"16 million .","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"The striking coverage losses led other Republican senators to oppose every plan but skinny repeal .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"Sen. Dean Heller","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"( R-NV )","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"also voted against repeal and replace and clean repeal","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"after holding a press conference last month with his state ' s Republican governor ,","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"saying","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"that the gains","depth":15},{"id":82,"text":"made","depth":16},{"id":83,"text":"after Nevada expanded Medicaid","depth":16},{"id":84,"text":"shouldn ' t be reversed .","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"\" We can ' t let fall behind the progress","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"we ' ve made in Nevada , \"","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"Heller said .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"Likewise , on the repeal-only legislation , Sen. Shelley Moore Capito","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"( R-WV )","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"said","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"she couldn ' t support it .","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"\" I did not come to Washington","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"to hurt people , \"","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"Senate leaders had also set their sights even bigger than Obamacare :","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"Their most ambitious proposal would have not only repealed and replaced much of the health care law","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"but also fundamentally overhauled Medicaid .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"The spending cuts","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"- $ 772 billion over 10 years , versus current law -","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"and a projected 15 million fewer enrollees also gave a critical mass of senators pause .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"On top of the raw numbers , Senate leaders were pushing to overhaul a 50-year-old program","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"that covers more than 70 million Americans","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"without holding a single hearing .","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"\" To do that","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"without holding a single hearing on what the implications would be for some of our most vulnerable citizens , for our rural hospitals , and our nursing homes , is not an approach","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"that I can endorse , \"","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"she said in recent days .","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"McCain decried the absurd Senate process ,","depth":5},{"id":109,"text":"and then he ended it","depth":5},{"id":110,"text":"He wasn ' t even supposed to be here .","depth":5},{"id":111,"text":"This month , he had emergency surgery for a blood clot","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"and then discovered","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"he had brain cancer .","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"He was thought to be out for weeks .","depth":6},{"id":115,"text":"His unexpectedly swift return to the Senate was supposed to be a boon for Senate Republican leaders ,","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"and it was -","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"until early Friday morning .","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"A few signs had suggested this possibility .","depth":5},{"id":119,"text":"On Tuesday ,","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"even as he voted to open the health care debate on the Senate floor ,","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"McCain hinted at what was to come .","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"He gave a floor speech after that vote","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"to open debate ,","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"calling for a return to regular order and a spirit of bipartisanship .","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"\" We try to do this","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"by coming up with a proposal behind closed doors in consultation with the administration ,","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"then springing it on skeptical members ,","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"trying to convince them","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"that it 's better than nothing , \"","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"he said in that floor speech .","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"\" That it 's better than nothing ?","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"Asking us to swallow our doubts","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"and force it past a unified opposition . \"","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"\" I do n't think","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"that 's going to work in the end , \"","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"he continued ,","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"\" and it probably should n't . \"","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"The speech , at the time , was widely condemned","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"- McCain had just voted to advance a bill","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"whose process he decried .","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"The original Senate repeal-and-replace bill had been negotiated and drafted entirely in secret for the previous two months .","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"No public hearings ,","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"no expert testimony .","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"Even as a number of Republican senators expressed discomfort ,","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"none of them stopped it .","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"That included McCain","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"- until Thursday night , after the most audacious ploy yet from Senate leadership .","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"Republican leaders ,","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"realizing","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"that they didn ' t have the votes for repeal and replace or repeal only ,","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"cooked up so-called \" skinny \" repeal","depth":14},{"id":152,"text":"- eliminating just Obamacare ' s individual mandate and a few other provisions .","depth":14},{"id":153,"text":"The bill was unveiled to the public late Thursday night , just hours before the first vote on it .","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"Senate leaders , meanwhile , were making a puzzling promise :","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"This bill wasn ' t actually intended to become law .","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"It was simply a vehicle","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"to enter conference negotiations with the House .","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"McCain ,","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"who had expressed apprehension about the Senate repeal-and-replace bill","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"and voted against repeal only ,","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"seemed thoroughly unsatisfied with \" skinny \" repeal as well .","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"Even tepid assurances from House leaders","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"that they would enter negotiations with the Senate","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"didn ' t assuage him .","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"\" I ' ve stated time and time again","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"that one of the major failures of Obamacare was that it was rammed through Congress by Democrats on a strict party-line basis","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"without a single Republican vote , \"","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"McCain said in a statement after his stunning vote .","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"\" We must now return to the correct way","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"of legislating","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"and send the bill back to committee ,","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"hold hearings ,","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"receive input from both sides of aisle ,","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"heed the recommendations of nation ' s governors ,","depth":14},{"id":175,"text":"and produce a bill","depth":15},{"id":176,"text":"that finally delivers affordable health care for the American people , \"","depth":15},{"id":177,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":178,"text":"\" We must do the hard work","depth":9},{"id":179,"text":"our citizens expect of us","depth":10},{"id":180,"text":"and deserve . \"","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"The floor vote was dramatic .","depth":2},{"id":182,"text":"It became clear something was amiss","depth":7},{"id":183,"text":"when McCain spoke briefly with the top Senate Democrat , Chuck Schumer ,","depth":7},{"id":184,"text":"and Schumer seemed elated .","depth":6},{"id":185,"text":"A conversation with the No . 2 Republican , John Cornyn , left Cornyn looking dour .","depth":5},{"id":186,"text":"As Republican leaders held a vote on a Democratic motion open for more than an hour ,","depth":5},{"id":187,"text":"McCain stood firm .","depth":5},{"id":188,"text":"His Arizona colleague , Jeff Flake , sat next to him for some time","depth":5},{"id":189,"text":"but seemed unable to get a word in .","depth":5},{"id":190,"text":"McCain gabbed with Sen. Lindsey Graham","depth":7},{"id":191,"text":"( R-SC ) ,","depth":7},{"id":192,"text":"his best friend in the Senate .","depth":6},{"id":193,"text":"The showdown was with Vice President Mike Pence ,","depth":10},{"id":194,"text":"present in the Senate","depth":10},{"id":195,"text":"in case he needed to cast a tiebreaker vote","depth":10},{"id":196,"text":"to give the \" skinny \" repeal bill a 51-vote majority .","depth":10},{"id":197,"text":"McCain and Pence spoke for nearly 30 minutes , in a conversation","depth":10},{"id":198,"text":"that at times seemed friendly","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"but then turned serious .","depth":11},{"id":200,"text":"McCain was insistent .","depth":9},{"id":201,"text":"Pence huddled with McConnell","depth":8},{"id":202,"text":"and left the floor for a time .","depth":8},{"id":203,"text":"McCain stepped into a back room ,","depth":9},{"id":204,"text":"believed to be taking a phone call .","depth":9},{"id":205,"text":"For a while , he chatted with Collins and Murkowski","depth":10},{"id":206,"text":"- the two senators","depth":11},{"id":207,"text":"he would soon join","depth":12},{"id":208,"text":"to kill \" skinny \" repeal -","depth":12},{"id":209,"text":"as they laughed","depth":10},{"id":210,"text":"and smiled .","depth":10},{"id":211,"text":"In the end , McCain stood dramatically before the Senate chair .","depth":9},{"id":212,"text":"He turned his thumb down .","depth":9},{"id":213,"text":"\" Skinny \" repeal","depth":10},{"id":214,"text":"- the Senate ' s last hope , for now ,","depth":11},{"id":215,"text":"to repeal Obamacare -","depth":11},{"id":216,"text":"was dead .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":433,"left":397,"right":432,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":397,"left":324,"right":396,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":324,"left":248,"right":323,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":248,"left":222,"right":247,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":222,"left":